WHEN starting new AI session:
  FIRST check existence of required files:
    - docs/AI_ASSIST.md
    - core-metrics-plus.php
    - docs/CHANGELOG.md
  
  IF any required file missing:
    THEN notify user and request file creation

WHEN making git changes:
  FIRST run "git status"
  THEN review changed files
  NEVER use "git add ."
  INSTEAD add files individually:
    FOR EACH changed_file:
      run "git add {changed_file}"

WHEN updating version:
  CHECK version numbers match in:
    - core-metrics-plus.php header
    - core-metrics-plus.php CMP_VERSION
    - docs/CHANGELOG.md
  
  IF versions don't match:
    THEN update all locations to match

WHEN creating commit:
  USE semantic commit types:
    - feat: new features
    - fix: bug fixes
    - docs: documentation
    - style: formatting
    - refactor: code restructure
    - test: testing
    - chore: maintenance
  
  FORMAT message as:
    type: Brief description
    
    - Detailed point 1
    - Detailed point 2

WHEN creating release:
  FIRST verify:
    - All version numbers match
    - CHANGELOG.md is updated
    - Tests pass
  THEN:
    - Create zip excluding ".*" and "__MACOSX"
    - Tag version
    - Push changes and tags
